Today I learnt about the use of css in the website. This styling is for making website attractive. Now I learnt how css play its role. Although I tried my best but I think my today's outcome isn't much good.  

code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Day 3</title>
    <style>
        h1{
            text-align: center;
        }
        img{
            height: 50%;
            width: 30%;
        }
        h3{
            margin: 0%;
            padding: 0%;
            display: inline-block;
            width: 19%;
            /* display: flex;
            flex-direction: row; */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello Everyone</h1>
    <div class="grt"><h2 class="grt">Welcome to a Car website</h2></div>
    <div class="top">
        <div style="display: inline-block;width: 33%;"><h2 style="margin: 0%;"><a href="F:/60%20days%20js/day%203/index.html">refresh link</a></h2></div>
        <div style="display: inline-block;width: 33%;"><h2 style="margin: 0%;text-align: center;"><a href="http://google.com">google.com</a></h2></div>
        <div style="display: inline-block;width: 33%;"><h2 style="margin: 0%;text-align: end;"><a href="http://youtube.com">youtube.com</a></h2></div>
    </div>
    <div id="divimg">

            <img src="./1996 dodge charger.jpg">
            <h3>1996 dodge charger</h3>

 
